The Kogi State Governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello has approved the appointment of four new Permanent Secretaries to fill some of the vacancies that exist in the Kogi State Civil Service as a result of the exit of the former Permanent Secretaries from Ankpa I, Igalamela-Odolu, Lokoja I and Kogi Local Government Areas, respectively. This was contained in a press statement issued on Friday by the Head of Civil Service, Kogi State, Mrs Deborah Ogunmola. Council Election: Kogi government lacks accountability ―… Kogi governor constitutes minimum wage committee Borno ex-gov Ali Modu Sheriff visits Kogi, condoles with Gov… PHCDA will revolutionise primary health care in Kogi ― Dr… ALSO READ: Buhari promises to bequeath free, fair elections to successor The new Permanent Secretaries are Hajia Ramatu Baba for Ankpa I, Abutu Jonah for Igalamela-Odolu, Abubakar Danlami Babamaaji for Lokoja I and Mohammed Musa Ohikwo for Kogi Local Government Area. The Head of Service express deep appreciation to His Excellency for approving the appointments of the new Permanent Secretaries, she congratulates the new Permanent Secretaries while imploring them to justify the immense confidence reposed in them as Permanent Secretaries, by being dedicated to their various duties and giving their total loyalty to the Administration of governor Bello at all times. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE